94@decorators.raise_if_nothing_inferred
95def unpack_infer(stmt, context: InferenceContext | None = None):
96 """recursively generate nodes inferred by the given statement.
97 If the inferred value is a list or a tuple, recurse on the elements
98 """
99 if isinstance(stmt, (List, Tuple)):
100 for elt in stmt.elts:
101 if elt is util.Uninferable:
102 yield elt
103 continue
104 yield from unpack_infer(elt, context)
105 return {"node": stmt, "context": context}
106 # if inferred is a final node, return it and stop
107 inferred = next(stmt.infer(context), util.Uninferable)
108 if inferred is stmt:
109 yield inferred
110 return {"node": stmt, "context": context}
111 # else, infer recursively, except Uninferable object that should be returned as is
112 for inferred in stmt.infer(context):
113 if isinstance(inferred, util.UninferableBase):
114 yield inferred
115 else:
116 yield from unpack_infer(inferred, context)
117
118 return {"node": stmt, "context": context}

121def are_exclusive(stmt1, stmt2, exceptions: list[str] | None = None) -> bool:
122 """return true if the two given statements are mutually exclusive
123
124 `exceptions` may be a list of exception names. If specified, discard If
125 branches and check one of the statement is in an exception handler catching
126 one of the given exceptions.
127
128 algorithm :
129 1) index stmt1's parents
130 2) climb among stmt2's parents until we find a common parent
131 3) if the common parent is a If or Try statement, look if nodes are
132 in exclusive branches
133 """
134 # index stmt1's parents
135 stmt1_parents = {}
136 children = {}
137 previous = stmt1
138 for node in stmt1.node_ancestors():
139 stmt1_parents[node] = 1
140 children[node] = previous
141 previous = node
142 # climb among stmt2's parents until we find a common parent
143 previous = stmt2
144 for node in stmt2.node_ancestors():
145 if node in stmt1_parents:
146 # if the common parent is a If or Try statement, look if
147 # nodes are in exclusive branches
148 if isinstance(node, If) and exceptions is None:
149 c2attr, c2node = node.locate_child(previous)
150 c1attr, c1node = node.locate_child(children[node])
151 if "test" in (c1attr, c2attr):
152 # If any node is `If.test`, then it must be inclusive with
153 # the other node (`If.body` and `If.orelse`)
154 return False
155 if c1attr != c2attr:
156 # different `If` branches (`If.body` and `If.orelse`)
157 return True
158 elif isinstance(node, Try):
159 c2attr, c2node = node.locate_child(previous)
160 c1attr, c1node = node.locate_child(children[node])
161 if c1node is not c2node:
162 first_in_body_caught_by_handlers = (
163 c2attr == "handlers"
164 and c1attr == "body"
165 and previous.catch(exceptions)
166 )
167 second_in_body_caught_by_handlers = (
168 c2attr == "body"
169 and c1attr == "handlers"
170 and children[node].catch(exceptions)
171 )
172 first_in_else_other_in_handlers = (
173 c2attr == "handlers" and c1attr == "orelse"
174 )
175 second_in_else_other_in_handlers = (
176 c2attr == "orelse" and c1attr == "handlers"
177 )
178 if any(
179 (
180 first_in_body_caught_by_handlers,
181 second_in_body_caught_by_handlers,
182 first_in_else_other_in_handlers,
183 second_in_else_other_in_handlers,
184 )
185 ):
186 return True
187 elif c2attr == "handlers" and c1attr == "handlers":
188 return previous is not children[node]
189 return False
190 previous = node
191 return False

196_SLICE_SENTINEL = object()
197
198
199def _slice_value(index, context: InferenceContext | None = None):
200 """Get the value of the given slice index."""
201
202 if isinstance(index, Const):
203 if isinstance(index.value, (int, type(None))):
204 return index.value
205 elif index is None:
206 return None
207 else:
208 # Try to infer what the index actually is.
209 # Since we can't return all the possible values,
210 # we'll stop at the first possible value.
211 try:
212 inferred = next(index.infer(context=context))
213 except (InferenceError, StopIteration):
214 pass
215 else:
216 if isinstance(inferred, Const):
217 if isinstance(inferred.value, (int, type(None))):
218 return inferred.value
219
220 # Use a sentinel, because None can be a valid
221 # value that this function can return,
222 # as it is the case for unspecified bounds.
223 return _SLICE_SENTINEL
224
225
226def _infer_slice(node, context: InferenceContext | None = None):
227 lower = _slice_value(node.lower, context)
228 upper = _slice_value(node.upper, context)
229 step = _slice_value(node.step, context)
230 if all(elem is not _SLICE_SENTINEL for elem in (lower, upper, step)):
231 return slice(lower, upper, step)
232
233 raise AstroidTypeError(
234 message="Could not infer slice used in subscript",
235 node=node,
236 index=node.parent,
237 context=context,
238 )
239
240
241def _container_getitem(instance, elts, index, context: InferenceContext | None = None):
242 """Get a slice or an item, using the given *index*, for the given sequence."""
243 try:
244 if isinstance(index, Slice):
245 index_slice = _infer_slice(index, context=context)
246 new_cls = instance.__class__()
247 new_cls.elts = elts[index_slice]
248 new_cls.parent = instance.parent
249 return new_cls
250 if isinstance(index, Const):
251 return elts[index.value]
252 except ValueError as exc:
253 raise AstroidValueError(
254 message="Slice {index!r} cannot index container",
255 node=instance,
256 index=index,
257 context=context,
258 ) from exc
259 except IndexError as exc:
260 raise AstroidIndexError(
261 message="Index {index!s} out of range",
262 node=instance,
263 index=index,
264 context=context,
265 ) from exc
266 except TypeError as exc:
267 raise AstroidTypeError(
268 message="Type error {error!r}", node=instance, index=index, context=context
269 ) from exc
270
271 raise AstroidTypeError(f"Could not use {index} as subscript index")

302 @classmethod
303 def from_elements(cls, elts: Iterable[Any]) -> Self:
304 """Create a node of this type from the given list of elements.
305
306 :param elts: The list of elements that the node should contain.
307
308 :returns: A new node containing the given elements.
309 """
310 node = cls(

313 parent=None,
314 end_lineno=None,
315 end_col_offset=None,
316 )
317 node.elts = [const_factory(e) if _is_const(e) else e for e in elts]

342 def get_children(self):
343 yield from self.elts

345 @decorators.raise_if_nothing_inferred
346 def _infer(
347 self,
348 context: InferenceContext | None = None,
349 **kwargs: Any,
350 ) -> Iterator[Self]:
351 has_starred_named_expr = any(
352 isinstance(e, (Starred, NamedExpr)) for e in self.elts
353 )
354 if has_starred_named_expr:
355 values = self._infer_sequence_helper(context)
356 new_seq = type(self)(
357 lineno=self.lineno,
358 col_offset=self.col_offset,
359 parent=self.parent,
360 end_lineno=self.end_lineno,
361 end_col_offset=self.end_col_offset,
362 )
363 new_seq.postinit(values)
364
365 yield new_seq
366 else:
367 yield self
368
369 def _infer_sequence_helper(
370 self, context: InferenceContext | None = None
371 ) -> list[SuccessfulInferenceResult]:
372 """Infer all values based on BaseContainer.elts."""
373 values = []
374
375 for elt in self.elts:
376 if isinstance(elt, Starred):
377 starred = util.safe_infer(elt.value, context)
378 if not starred:
379 raise InferenceError(node=self, context=context)
380 if not hasattr(starred, "elts"):
381 raise InferenceError(node=self, context=context)
382 # TODO: fresh context?
383 values.extend(starred._infer_sequence_helper(context))
384 elif isinstance(elt, NamedExpr):
385 value = util.safe_infer(elt.value, context)
386 if not value:
387 raise InferenceError(node=self, context=context)
388 values.append(value)
389 else:
390 values.append(elt)
391 return values

413 >>> list(node.get_children())[0].as_string()
414 'variable'
415 """

441 """Returns the assigned statement (non inferred) according to the assignment type.
442 See astroid/protocols.py for actual implementation.

445 @decorators.raise_if_nothing_inferred
446 @decorators.path_wrapper
447 def _infer(
448 self, context: InferenceContext | None = None, **kwargs: Any
449 ) -> Generator[InferenceResult, None, InferenceErrorInfo | None]:
450 """Infer an AssignName: need to inspect the RHS part of the
451 assign node.
452 """
453 if isinstance(self.parent, AugAssign):
454 return self.parent.infer(context)
455
456 stmts = list(self.assigned_stmts(context=context))
457 return _infer_stmts(stmts, context)
458
459 @decorators.raise_if_nothing_inferred
460 def infer_lhs(
461 self, context: InferenceContext | None = None, **kwargs: Any
462 ) -> Generator[InferenceResult, None, InferenceErrorInfo | None]:
463 """Infer a Name: use name lookup rules.
464
465 Same implementation as Name._infer."""
466 # pylint: disable=import-outside-toplevel
467 from astroid.constraint import get_constraints
468 from astroid.helpers import _higher_function_scope
469
470 frame, stmts = self.lookup(self.name)
471 if not stmts:
472 # Try to see if the name is enclosed in a nested function
473 # and use the higher (first function) scope for searching.
474 parent_function = _higher_function_scope(self.scope())
475 if parent_function:
476 _, stmts = parent_function.lookup(self.name)
477
478 if not stmts:
479 raise NameInferenceError(
480 name=self.name, scope=self.scope(), context=context
481 )
482 context = copy_context(context)
483 context.lookupname = self.name
484 context.constraints[self.name] = get_constraints(self, frame)
485
486 return _infer_stmts(stmts, context, frame)

607class Arguments(
608 _base_nodes.AssignTypeNode
609): # pylint: disable=too-many-instance-attributes
610 """Class representing an :class:`ast.arguments` node.
611
612 An :class:`Arguments` node represents that arguments in a
613 function definition.
614
615 >>> import astroid
616 >>> node = astroid.extract_node('def foo(bar): pass')
617 >>> node
618 <FunctionDef.foo l.1 at 0x7effe1db8198>
619 >>> node.args
620 <Arguments l.1 at 0x7effe1db82e8>
621 """
622
623 # Python 3.4+ uses a different approach regarding annotations,
624 # each argument is a new class, _ast.arg, which exposes an
625 # 'annotation' attribute. In astroid though, arguments are exposed
626 # as is in the Arguments node and the only way to expose annotations
627 # is by using something similar with Python 3.3:
628 # - we expose 'varargannotation' and 'kwargannotation' of annotations
629 # of varargs and kwargs.
630 # - we expose 'annotation', a list with annotations for
631 # for each normal argument. If an argument doesn't have an
632 # annotation, its value will be None.
633 _astroid_fields = (
634 "args",
635 "defaults",
636 "kwonlyargs",
637 "posonlyargs",
638 "posonlyargs_annotations",
639 "kw_defaults",
640 "annotations",
641 "varargannotation",
642 "kwargannotation",
643 "kwonlyargs_annotations",
644 "type_comment_args",
645 "type_comment_kwonlyargs",
646 "type_comment_posonlyargs",
647 )
648
649 _other_fields = ("vararg", "kwarg")

657 incomplete signature information.
658 """

770 type_comment_args = []

773 type_comment_kwonlyargs = []
774 self.type_comment_kwonlyargs = type_comment_kwonlyargs
775 if type_comment_posonlyargs is None:
776 type_comment_posonlyargs = []
777 self.type_comment_posonlyargs = type_comment_posonlyargs

784 def _infer_name(self, frame, name):
785 if self.parent is frame:
786 return name
787 return None

789 @cached_property
790 def fromlineno(self) -> int:
791 """The first line that this node appears on in the source code.
792
793 Can also return 0 if the line can not be determined.
794 """
795 lineno = super().fromlineno
796 return max(lineno, self.parent.fromlineno or 0)
797
798 @cached_property
799 def arguments(self):
800 """Get all the arguments for this node. This includes:
801 * Positional only arguments
802 * Positional arguments
803 * Keyword arguments
804 * Variable arguments (.e.g *args)
805 * Variable keyword arguments (e.g **kwargs)
806 """
807 retval = list(itertools.chain((self.posonlyargs or ()), (self.args or ())))
808 if self.vararg_node:
809 retval.append(self.vararg_node)
810 retval += self.kwonlyargs or ()
811 if self.kwarg_node:
812 retval.append(self.kwarg_node)
813
814 return retval
815
816 def format_args(self, *, skippable_names: set[str] | None = None) -> str:
817 """Get the arguments formatted as string.
818
819 :returns: The formatted arguments.
820 :rtype: str
821 """
822 result = []
823 positional_only_defaults = []
824 positional_or_keyword_defaults = self.defaults
825 if self.defaults:
826 args = self.args or []
827 positional_or_keyword_defaults = self.defaults[-len(args) :]
828 positional_only_defaults = self.defaults[: len(self.defaults) - len(args)]
829
830 if self.posonlyargs:
831 result.append(
832 _format_args(
833 self.posonlyargs,
834 positional_only_defaults,
835 self.posonlyargs_annotations,
836 skippable_names=skippable_names,
837 )
838 )
839 result.append("/")
840 if self.args:
841 result.append(
842 _format_args(
843 self.args,
844 positional_or_keyword_defaults,
845 getattr(self, "annotations", None),
846 skippable_names=skippable_names,
847 )
848 )
849 if self.vararg:
850 result.append(f"*{self.vararg}")
851 if self.kwonlyargs:
852 if not self.vararg:
853 result.append("*")
854 result.append(
855 _format_args(
856 self.kwonlyargs,
857 self.kw_defaults,
858 self.kwonlyargs_annotations,
859 skippable_names=skippable_names,
860 )
861 )
862 if self.kwarg:
863 result.append(f"**{self.kwarg}")
864 return ", ".join(result)

866 def _get_arguments_data(
867 self,
868 ) -> tuple[
869 dict[str, tuple[str | None, str | None]],
870 dict[str, tuple[str | None, str | None]],
871 ]:
872 """Get the arguments as dictionary with information about typing and defaults.
873
874 The return tuple contains a dictionary for positional and keyword arguments with their typing
875 and their default value, if any.
876 The method follows a similar order as format_args but instead of formatting into a string it
877 returns the data that is used to do so.
878 """
879 pos_only: dict[str, tuple[str | None, str | None]] = {}
880 kw_only: dict[str, tuple[str | None, str | None]] = {}
881
882 # Setup and match defaults with arguments
883 positional_only_defaults = []
884 positional_or_keyword_defaults = self.defaults
885 if self.defaults:
886 args = self.args or []
887 positional_or_keyword_defaults = self.defaults[-len(args) :]
888 positional_only_defaults = self.defaults[: len(self.defaults) - len(args)]
889
890 for index, posonly in enumerate(self.posonlyargs):
891 annotation, default = self.posonlyargs_annotations[index], None
892 if annotation is not None:
893 annotation = annotation.as_string()
894 if positional_only_defaults:
895 default = positional_only_defaults[index].as_string()
896 pos_only[posonly.name] = (annotation, default)
897
898 for index, arg in enumerate(self.args):
899 annotation, default = self.annotations[index], None
900 if annotation is not None:
901 annotation = annotation.as_string()
902 if positional_or_keyword_defaults:
903 defaults_offset = len(self.args) - len(positional_or_keyword_defaults)
904 default_index = index - defaults_offset
905 if (
906 default_index > -1
907 and positional_or_keyword_defaults[default_index] is not None
908 ):
909 default = positional_or_keyword_defaults[default_index].as_string()
910 pos_only[arg.name] = (annotation, default)
911
912 if self.vararg:
913 annotation = self.varargannotation
914 if annotation is not None:
915 annotation = annotation.as_string()
916 pos_only[self.vararg] = (annotation, None)
917
918 for index, kwarg in enumerate(self.kwonlyargs):
919 annotation = self.kwonlyargs_annotations[index]
920 if annotation is not None:
921 annotation = annotation.as_string()
922 default = self.kw_defaults[index]
923 if default is not None:
924 default = default.as_string()
925 kw_only[kwarg.name] = (annotation, default)
926
927 if self.kwarg:
928 annotation = self.kwargannotation
929 if annotation is not None:
930 annotation = annotation.as_string()
931 kw_only[self.kwarg] = (annotation, None)
932
933 return pos_only, kw_only
934
935 def default_value(self, argname):
936 """Get the default value for an argument.
937
938 :param argname: The name of the argument to get the default value for.
939 :type argname: str
940
941 :raises NoDefault: If there is no default value defined for the
942 given argument.
943 """
944 args = [
945 arg for arg in self.arguments if arg.name not in [self.vararg, self.kwarg]
946 ]
947
948 index = _find_arg(argname, self.kwonlyargs)[0]
949 if (index is not None) and (len(self.kw_defaults) > index):
950 if self.kw_defaults[index] is not None:
951 return self.kw_defaults[index]
952 raise NoDefault(func=self.parent, name=argname)
953
954 index = _find_arg(argname, args)[0]
955 if index is not None:
956 idx = index - (len(args) - len(self.defaults) - len(self.kw_defaults))
957 if idx >= 0:
958 return self.defaults[idx]
959
960 raise NoDefault(func=self.parent, name=argname)
961
962 def is_argument(self, name) -> bool:
963 """Check if the given name is defined in the arguments.
964
965 :param name: The name to check for.
966 :type name: str
967
968 :returns: Whether the given name is defined in the arguments,
969 """
970 if name == self.vararg:
971 return True
972 if name == self.kwarg:
973 return True
974 return self.find_argname(name)[1] is not None
975
976 def find_argname(self, argname, rec=DEPRECATED_ARGUMENT_DEFAULT):
977 """Get the index and :class:`AssignName` node for given name.
978
979 :param argname: The name of the argument to search for.
980 :type argname: str
981
982 :returns: The index and node for the argument.
983 :rtype: tuple(str or None, AssignName or None)
984 """
985 if rec != DEPRECATED_ARGUMENT_DEFAULT: # pragma: no cover
986 warnings.warn(
987 "The rec argument will be removed in astroid 3.1.",
988 DeprecationWarning,
989 stacklevel=2,
990 )
991 if self.arguments:
992 index, argument = _find_arg(argname, self.arguments)
993 if argument:
994 return index, argument
995 return None, None

997 def get_children(self):
998 yield from self.posonlyargs or ()
999
1000 for elt in self.posonlyargs_annotations:
1001 if elt is not None:
1002 yield elt
1003
1004 yield from self.args or ()
1005
1006 if self.defaults is not None:
1007 yield from self.defaults
1008 yield from self.kwonlyargs
1009
1010 for elt in self.kw_defaults or ():
1011 if elt is not None:
1012 yield elt
1013
1014 for elt in self.annotations:
1015 if elt is not None:
1016 yield elt
1017
1018 if self.varargannotation is not None:
1019 yield self.varargannotation
1020
1021 if self.kwargannotation is not None:
1022 yield self.kwargannotation
1023
1024 for elt in self.kwonlyargs_annotations:
1025 if elt is not None:
1026 yield elt

1030 self: nodes.Arguments, context: InferenceContext | None = None, **kwargs: Any
1031 ) -> Generator[InferenceResult]:
1032 # pylint: disable-next=import-outside-toplevel
1033 from astroid.protocols import _arguments_infer_argname
1034

1040def _find_arg(argname, args):
1041 for i, arg in enumerate(args):
1042 if arg.name == argname:
1043 return i, arg
1044 return None, None
1045
1046
1047def _format_args(
1048 args, defaults=None, annotations=None, skippable_names: set[str] | None = None
1049) -> str:
1050 if skippable_names is None:
1051 skippable_names = set()
1052 values = []
1053 if args is None:
1054 return ""
1055 if annotations is None:
1056 annotations = []
1057 if defaults is not None:
1058 default_offset = len(args) - len(defaults)
1059 else:
1060 default_offset = None
1061 packed = itertools.zip_longest(args, annotations)
1062 for i, (arg, annotation) in enumerate(packed):
1063 if arg.name in skippable_names:
1064 continue
1065 if isinstance(arg, Tuple):
1066 values.append(f"({_format_args(arg.elts)})")
1067 else:
1068 argname = arg.name
1069 default_sep = "="
1070 if annotation is not None:
1071 argname += ": " + annotation.as_string()
1072 default_sep = " = "
1073 values.append(argname)
1074
1075 if default_offset is not None and i >= default_offset:
1076 if defaults[i - default_offset] is not None:
1077 values[-1] += default_sep + defaults[i - default_offset].as_string()
1078 return ", ".join(values)

1081def _infer_attribute(
1082 node: nodes.AssignAttr | nodes.Attribute,
1083 context: InferenceContext | None = None,
1084 **kwargs: Any,
1085) -> Generator[InferenceResult, None, InferenceErrorInfo]:
1086 """Infer an AssignAttr/Attribute node by using getattr on the associated object."""
1087 # pylint: disable=import-outside-toplevel
1088 from astroid.constraint import get_constraints
1089 from astroid.nodes import ClassDef
1090
1091 for owner in node.expr.infer(context):
1092 if isinstance(owner, util.UninferableBase):
1093 yield owner
1094 continue
1095
1096 context = copy_context(context)
1097 old_boundnode = context.boundnode
1098 try:
1099 context.boundnode = owner
1100 if isinstance(owner, (ClassDef, Instance)):
1101 frame = owner if isinstance(owner, ClassDef) else owner._proxied
1102 context.constraints[node.attrname] = get_constraints(node, frame=frame)
1103 if node.attrname == "argv" and owner.name == "sys":
1104 # sys.argv will never be inferable during static analysis
1105 # It's value would be the args passed to the linter itself
1106 yield util.Uninferable
1107 else:
1108 yield from owner.igetattr(node.attrname, context)
1109 except (
1110 AttributeInferenceError,
1111 InferenceError,
1112 AttributeError,
1113 ):
1114 pass
1115 finally:
1116 context.boundnode = old_boundnode
1117 return InferenceErrorInfo(node=node, context=context)

1383 def type_errors(
1384 self, context: InferenceContext | None = None
1385 ) -> list[util.BadBinaryOperationMessage]:
1386 """Get a list of type errors which can occur during inference.
1387
1388 Each TypeError is represented by a :class:`BadBinaryOperationMessage` ,
1389 which holds the original exception.
1390
1391 If any inferred result is uninferable, an empty list is returned.
1392 """
1393 bad = []
1394 try:
1395 for result in self._infer_augassign(context=context):
1396 if result is util.Uninferable:
1397 raise InferenceError
1398 if isinstance(result, util.BadBinaryOperationMessage):
1399 bad.append(result)

1418 def _infer_augassign(
1419 self, context: InferenceContext | None = None
1420 ) -> Generator[InferenceResult | util.BadBinaryOperationMessage]:
1421 """Inference logic for augmented binary operations."""
1422 context = context or InferenceContext()
1423
1424 rhs_context = context.clone()
1425
1426 lhs_iter = self.target.infer_lhs(context=context)
1427 rhs_iter = self.value.infer(context=rhs_context)
1428
1429 for lhs, rhs in itertools.product(lhs_iter, rhs_iter):
1430 if any(isinstance(value, util.UninferableBase) for value in (rhs, lhs)):
1431 # Don't know how to process this.
1432 yield util.Uninferable
1433 return
1434
1435 try:
1436 yield from self._infer_binary_operation(
1437 left=lhs,
1438 right=rhs,
1439 binary_opnode=self,
1440 context=context,
1441 flow_factory=self._get_aug_flow,
1442 )
1443 except _NonDeducibleTypeHierarchy:
1444 yield util.Uninferable

1446 @decorators.raise_if_nothing_inferred
1447 @decorators.path_wrapper
1448 def _infer(
1449 self: nodes.AugAssign, context: InferenceContext | None = None, **kwargs: Any
1450 ) -> Generator[InferenceResult]:
1451 return self._filter_operation_errors(
1452 self._infer_augassign, context, util.BadBinaryOperationMessage
1453 )

1509 If any inferred result is uninferable, an empty list is returned.
1510 """
1511 bad = []
1512 try:
1513 for result in self._infer_binop(context=context):
1514 if result is util.Uninferable:
1515 raise InferenceError
1516 if isinstance(result, util.BadBinaryOperationMessage):
1517 bad.append(result)
1518 except InferenceError:
1519 return []
1520 return bad
1521
1522 def get_children(self):
1523 yield self.left
1524 yield self.right
1525
1526 def op_precedence(self):
1527 return OP_PRECEDENCE[self.op]
1528
1529 def op_left_associative(self) -> bool:
1530 # 2**3**4 == 2**(3**4)
1531 return self.op != "**"
1532
1533 def _infer_binop(
1534 self, context: InferenceContext | None = None, **kwargs: Any
1535 ) -> Generator[InferenceResult]:
1536 """Binary operation inference logic."""
1537 left = self.left
1538 right = self.right
1539
1540 # we use two separate contexts for evaluating lhs and rhs because
1541 # 1. evaluating lhs may leave some undesired entries in context.path
1542 # which may not let us infer right value of rhs
1543 context = context or InferenceContext()
1544 lhs_context = copy_context(context)
1545 rhs_context = copy_context(context)
1546 lhs_iter = left.infer(context=lhs_context)
1547 rhs_iter = right.infer(context=rhs_context)
1548 for lhs, rhs in itertools.product(lhs_iter, rhs_iter):
1549 if any(isinstance(value, util.UninferableBase) for value in (rhs, lhs)):
1550 # Don't know how to process this.
1551 yield util.Uninferable
1552 return
1553
1554 try:
1555 yield from self._infer_binary_operation(
1556 lhs, rhs, self, context, self._get_binop_flow
1557 )
1558 except _NonDeducibleTypeHierarchy:
1559 yield util.Uninferable
1560
1561 @decorators.yes_if_nothing_inferred
1562 @decorators.path_wrapper
1563 def _infer(
1564 self: nodes.BinOp, context: InferenceContext | None = None, **kwargs: Any
1565 ) -> Generator[InferenceResult]:
1566 return self._filter_operation_errors(
1567 self._infer_binop, context, util.BadBinaryOperationMessage
1568 )

1638 @decorators.raise_if_nothing_inferred
1639 @decorators.path_wrapper
1640 def _infer(
1641 self: nodes.BoolOp, context: InferenceContext | None = None, **kwargs: Any
1642 ) -> Generator[InferenceResult, None, InferenceErrorInfo | None]:
1643 """Infer a boolean operation (and / or / not).
1644
1645 The function will calculate the boolean operation
1646 for all pairs generated through inference for each component
1647 node.
1648 """
1649 values = self.values
1650 if self.op == "or":
1651 predicate = operator.truth
1652 else:
1653 predicate = operator.not_
1654
1655 try:
1656 inferred_values = [value.infer(context=context) for value in values]
1657 except InferenceError:
1658 yield util.Uninferable
1659 return None
1660
1661 for pair in itertools.product(*inferred_values):
1662 if any(isinstance(item, util.UninferableBase) for item in pair):
1663 # Can't infer the final result, just yield Uninferable.
1664 yield util.Uninferable
1665 continue
1666
1667 bool_values = [item.bool_value() for item in pair]
1668 if any(isinstance(item, util.UninferableBase) for item in bool_values):
1669 # Can't infer the final result, just yield Uninferable.
1670 yield util.Uninferable
1671 continue
1672
1673 # Since the boolean operations are short circuited operations,
1674 # this code yields the first value for which the predicate is True
1675 # and if no value respected the predicate, then the last value will
1676 # be returned (or Uninferable if there was no last value).
1677 # This is conforming to the semantics of `and` and `or`:
1678 # 1 and 0 -> 1
1679 # 0 and 1 -> 0
1680 # 1 or 0 -> 1
1681 # 0 or 1 -> 1
1682 value = util.Uninferable
1683 for value, bool_value in zip(pair, bool_values):
1684 if predicate(bool_value):
1685 yield value
1686 break
1687 else:
1688 yield value
1689
1690 return InferenceErrorInfo(node=self, context=context)
1691

1755 callcontext = copy_context(context)
1756 callcontext.boundnode = None

1758 callcontext.extra_context = self._populate_context_lookup(context.clone())

1776 def _populate_context_lookup(self, context: InferenceContext | None):
1777 """Allows context to be saved for later for inference inside a function."""
1778 context_lookup: dict[InferenceResult, InferenceContext] = {}
1779 if context is None:
1780 return context_lookup
1781 for arg in self.args:
1782 if isinstance(arg, Starred):
1783 context_lookup[arg.value] = context
1784 else:
1785 context_lookup[arg] = context
1786 keywords = self.keywords if self.keywords is not None else []
1787 for keyword in keywords:
1788 context_lookup[keyword.value] = context
1789 return context_lookup

1864 def _do_compare(
1865 self,
1866 left_iter: Iterable[InferenceResult],
1867 op: str,
1868 right_iter: Iterable[InferenceResult],
1869 ) -> bool | util.UninferableBase:
1870 """
1871 If all possible combinations are either True or False, return that:
1872 >>> _do_compare([1, 2], '<=', [3, 4])
1873 True
1874 >>> _do_compare([1, 2], '==', [3, 4])
1875 False
1876
1877 If any item is uninferable, or if some combinations are True and some
1878 are False, return Uninferable:
1879 >>> _do_compare([1, 3], '<=', [2, 4])
1880 util.Uninferable
1881 """
1882 retval: bool | None = None
1883 if op in UNINFERABLE_OPS:
1884 return util.Uninferable
1885 op_func = COMPARE_OPS[op]
1886
1887 for left, right in itertools.product(left_iter, right_iter):
1888 if isinstance(left, util.UninferableBase) or isinstance(
1889 right, util.UninferableBase
1890 ):
1891 return util.Uninferable
1892
1893 try:
1894 left, right = self._to_literal(left), self._to_literal(right)
1895 except (SyntaxError, ValueError, AttributeError):
1896 return util.Uninferable
1897
1898 try:
1899 expr = op_func(left, right)
1900 except TypeError as exc:
1901 raise AstroidTypeError from exc
1902
1903 if retval is None:
1904 retval = expr
1905 elif retval != expr:
1906 return util.Uninferable
1907 # (or both, but "True | False" is basically the same)
1908
1909 assert retval is not None
1910 return retval # it was all the same value
1911
1912 def _infer(
1913 self, context: InferenceContext | None = None, **kwargs: Any
1914 ) -> Generator[nodes.Const | util.UninferableBase]:
1915 """Chained comparison inference logic."""
1916 retval: bool | util.UninferableBase = True
1917
1918 ops = self.ops
1919 left_node = self.left
1920 lhs = list(left_node.infer(context=context))
1921 # should we break early if first element is uninferable?
1922 for op, right_node in ops:
1923 # eagerly evaluate rhs so that values can be re-used as lhs
1924 rhs = list(right_node.infer(context=context))
1925 try:
1926 retval = self._do_compare(lhs, op, rhs)
1927 except AstroidTypeError:
1928 retval = util.Uninferable
1929 break
1930 if retval is not True:
1931 break # short-circuit
1932 lhs = rhs # continue
1933 if retval is util.Uninferable:
1934 yield retval # type: ignore[misc]
1935 else:
1936 yield Const(retval)

2393 def getitem(
2394 self, index: Const | Slice, context: InferenceContext | None = None
2395 ) -> NodeNG:
2396 """Get an item from this node.
2397
2398 :param index: The node to use as a subscript index.
2399
2400 :raises AstroidTypeError: When the given index cannot be used as a
2401 subscript index, or if this node is not subscriptable.
2402 :raises AstroidIndexError: If the given index does not exist in the
2403 dictionary.
2404 """
2405 for key, value in self.items:
2406 # TODO(cpopa): no support for overriding yet, {1:2, **{1: 3}}.
2407 if isinstance(key, DictUnpack):
2408 inferred_value = util.safe_infer(value, context)
2409 if not isinstance(inferred_value, Dict):
2410 continue
2411
2412 try:
2413 return inferred_value.getitem(index, context)
2414 except (AstroidTypeError, AstroidIndexError):
2415 continue
2416
2417 for inferredkey in key.infer(context):
2418 if isinstance(inferredkey, util.UninferableBase):
2419 continue
2420 if isinstance(inferredkey, Const) and isinstance(index, Const):
2421 if inferredkey.value == index.value:
2422 return value
2423
2424 raise AstroidIndexError(index)
2425
2426 def bool_value(self, context: InferenceContext | None = None):
2427 """Determine the boolean value of this node.
2428
2429 :returns: The boolean value of this node.
2430 :rtype: bool
2431 """
2432 return bool(self.items)
2433
2434 def _infer(
2435 self, context: InferenceContext | None = None, **kwargs: Any
2436 ) -> Iterator[nodes.Dict]:
2437 if not any(isinstance(k, DictUnpack) for k, _ in self.items):
2438 yield self
2439 else:
2440 items = self._infer_map(context)
2441 new_seq = type(self)(
2442 lineno=self.lineno,
2443 col_offset=self.col_offset,
2444 parent=self.parent,
2445 end_lineno=self.end_lineno,
2446 end_col_offset=self.end_col_offset,
2447 )
2448 new_seq.postinit(list(items.items()))
2449 yield new_seq
2450
2451 @staticmethod
2452 def _update_with_replacement(
2453 lhs_dict: dict[SuccessfulInferenceResult, SuccessfulInferenceResult],
2454 rhs_dict: dict[SuccessfulInferenceResult, SuccessfulInferenceResult],
2455 ) -> dict[SuccessfulInferenceResult, SuccessfulInferenceResult]:
2456 """Delete nodes that equate to duplicate keys.
2457
2458 Since an astroid node doesn't 'equal' another node with the same value,
2459 this function uses the as_string method to make sure duplicate keys
2460 don't get through
2461
2462 Note that both the key and the value are astroid nodes
2463
2464 Fixes issue with DictUnpack causing duplicate keys
2465 in inferred Dict items
2466
2467 :param lhs_dict: Dictionary to 'merge' nodes into
2468 :param rhs_dict: Dictionary with nodes to pull from
2469 :return : merged dictionary of nodes
2470 """
2471 combined_dict = itertools.chain(lhs_dict.items(), rhs_dict.items())
2472 # Overwrite keys which have the same string values
2473 string_map = {key.as_string(): (key, value) for key, value in combined_dict}
2474 # Return to dictionary
2475 return dict(string_map.values())
2476
2477 def _infer_map(
2478 self, context: InferenceContext | None
2479 ) -> dict[SuccessfulInferenceResult, SuccessfulInferenceResult]:
2480 """Infer all values based on Dict.items."""
2481 values: dict[SuccessfulInferenceResult, SuccessfulInferenceResult] = {}
2482 for name, value in self.items:
2483 if isinstance(name, DictUnpack):
2484 double_starred = util.safe_infer(value, context)
2485 if not double_starred:
2486 raise InferenceError
2487 if not isinstance(double_starred, Dict):
2488 raise InferenceError(node=self, context=context)
2489 unpack_items = double_starred._infer_map(context)
2490 values = self._update_with_replacement(values, unpack_items)
2491 else:
2492 key = util.safe_infer(name, context=context)
2493 safe_value = util.safe_infer(value, context=context)
2494 if any(not elem for elem in (key, safe_value)):
2495 raise InferenceError(node=self, context=context)
2496 # safe_value is SuccessfulInferenceResult as bool(Uninferable) == False
2497 values = self._update_with_replacement(values, {key: safe_value})
2498 return values

3005
3006 body: list[NodeNG]
3007 """The contents of the block."""
3008
3009 orelse: list[NodeNG]
3010 """The contents of the ``else`` block."""
3011

3025 def block_range(self, lineno: int) -> tuple[int, int]:
3026 """Get a range from the given line number to where this node ends.
3027
3028 :param lineno: The line number to start the range at.
3029
3030 :returns: The range of line numbers that this node belongs to,
3031 starting at the given line number.
3032 """
3033 if lineno == self.body[0].fromlineno:
3034 return lineno, lineno
3035 if lineno <= self.body[-1].tolineno:

3037 return self._elsed_block_range(lineno, self.orelse, self.body[0].fromlineno - 1)

3061 >>> import astroid

3063 >>> node
3064 <IfExp l.1 at 0x7f23b2e9dbe0>
3065 """
3066
3067 _astroid_fields = ("test", "body", "orelse")
3068
3069 test: NodeNG
3070 """The condition that the statement tests."""
3071
3072 body: NodeNG
3073 """The contents of the block."""
3074
3075 orelse: NodeNG
3076 """The contents of the ``else`` block."""
3077
3078 def postinit(self, test: NodeNG, body: NodeNG, orelse: NodeNG) -> None:
3079 self.test = test
3080 self.body = body
3081 self.orelse = orelse

3088 def op_left_associative(self) -> Literal[False]:
3089 # `1 if True else 2 if False else 3` is parsed as
3090 # `1 if True else (2 if False else 3)`
3091 return False
3092
3093 @decorators.raise_if_nothing_inferred
3094 def _infer(
3095 self, context: InferenceContext | None = None, **kwargs: Any
3096 ) -> Generator[InferenceResult]:
3097 """Support IfExp inference.
3098
3099 If we can't infer the truthiness of the condition, we default
3100 to inferring both branches. Otherwise, we infer either branch
3101 depending on the condition.
3102 """
3103 both_branches = False
3104 # We use two separate contexts for evaluating lhs and rhs because
3105 # evaluating lhs may leave some undesired entries in context.path
3106 # which may not let us infer right value of rhs.
3107
3108 context = context or InferenceContext()
3109 lhs_context = copy_context(context)
3110 rhs_context = copy_context(context)
3111 try:
3112 test = next(self.test.infer(context=context.clone()))
3113 except (InferenceError, StopIteration):
3114 both_branches = True
3115 else:
3116 if not isinstance(test, util.UninferableBase):
3117 if test.bool_value():
3118 yield from self.body.infer(context=lhs_context)
3119 else:
3120 yield from self.orelse.infer(context=rhs_context)
3121 else:
3122 both_branches = True
3123 if both_branches:
3124 yield from self.body.infer(context=lhs_context)
3125 yield from self.orelse.infer(context=rhs_context)

3711 def _infer_subscript(
3712 self, context: InferenceContext | None = None, **kwargs: Any
3713 ) -> Generator[InferenceResult, None, InferenceErrorInfo | None]:
3714 """Inference for subscripts.
3715
3716 We're understanding if the index is a Const
3717 or a slice, passing the result of inference
3718 to the value's `getitem` method, which should
3719 handle each supported index type accordingly.
3720 """
3721 from astroid import helpers # pylint: disable=import-outside-toplevel
3722
3723 found_one = False
3724 for value in self.value.infer(context):
3725 if isinstance(value, util.UninferableBase):
3726 yield util.Uninferable
3727 return None
3728 for index in self.slice.infer(context):
3729 if isinstance(index, util.UninferableBase):
3730 yield util.Uninferable
3731 return None
3732
3733 # Try to deduce the index value.
3734 index_value = self._SUBSCRIPT_SENTINEL
3735 if value.__class__ == Instance:
3736 index_value = index
3737 elif index.__class__ == Instance:
3738 instance_as_index = helpers.class_instance_as_index(index)
3739 if instance_as_index:
3740 index_value = instance_as_index
3741 else:
3742 index_value = index
3743
3744 if index_value is self._SUBSCRIPT_SENTINEL:
3745 raise InferenceError(node=self, context=context)
3746
3747 try:
3748 assigned = value.getitem(index_value, context)
3749 except (
3750 AstroidTypeError,
3751 AstroidIndexError,
3752 AstroidValueError,
3753 AttributeInferenceError,
3754 AttributeError,
3755 ) as exc:
3756 raise InferenceError(node=self, context=context) from exc
3757
3758 # Prevent inferring if the inferred subscript
3759 # is the same as the original subscripted object.
3760 if self is assigned or isinstance(assigned, util.UninferableBase):
3761 yield util.Uninferable
3762 return None
3763 yield from assigned.infer(context)
3764 found_one = True
3765
3766 if found_one:
3767 return InferenceErrorInfo(node=self, context=context)
3768 return None
3769
3770 @decorators.raise_if_nothing_inferred
3771 @decorators.path_wrapper
3772 def _infer(self, context: InferenceContext | None = None, **kwargs: Any):
3773 return self._infer_subscript(context, **kwargs)
3774
3775 @decorators.raise_if_nothing_inferred
3776 def infer_lhs(self, context: InferenceContext | None = None, **kwargs: Any):
3777 return self._infer_subscript(context, **kwargs)

4268 def type_errors(
4269 self, context: InferenceContext | None = None
4270 ) -> list[util.BadUnaryOperationMessage]:
4271 """Get a list of type errors which can occur during inference.
4272
4273 Each TypeError is represented by a :class:`BadUnaryOperationMessage`,
4274 which holds the original exception.
4275
4276 If any inferred result is uninferable, an empty list is returned.
4277 """
4278 bad = []
4279 try:
4280 for result in self._infer_unaryop(context=context):
4281 if result is util.Uninferable:
4282 raise InferenceError
4283 if isinstance(result, util.BadUnaryOperationMessage):
4284 bad.append(result)

4298 def _infer_unaryop(
4299 self: nodes.UnaryOp, context: InferenceContext | None = None, **kwargs: Any
4300 ) -> Generator[
4301 InferenceResult | util.BadUnaryOperationMessage, None, InferenceErrorInfo
4302 ]:
4303 """Infer what an UnaryOp should return when evaluated."""
4304 from astroid.nodes import ClassDef # pylint: disable=import-outside-toplevel
4305
4306 for operand in self.operand.infer(context):
4307 try:
4308 yield operand.infer_unary_op(self.op)
4309 except TypeError as exc:
4310 # The operand doesn't support this operation.
4311 yield util.BadUnaryOperationMessage(operand, self.op, exc)
4312 except AttributeError as exc:
4313 meth = UNARY_OP_METHOD[self.op]
4314 if meth is None:
4315 # `not node`. Determine node's boolean
4316 # value and negate its result, unless it is
4317 # Uninferable, which will be returned as is.
4318 bool_value = operand.bool_value()
4319 if not isinstance(bool_value, util.UninferableBase):
4320 yield const_factory(not bool_value)
4321 else:
4322 yield util.Uninferable
4323 else:
4324 if not isinstance(operand, (Instance, ClassDef)):
4325 # The operation was used on something which
4326 # doesn't support it.
4327 yield util.BadUnaryOperationMessage(operand, self.op, exc)
4328 continue
4329
4330 try:
4331 try:
4332 methods = dunder_lookup.lookup(operand, meth)
4333 except AttributeInferenceError:
4334 yield util.BadUnaryOperationMessage(operand, self.op, exc)
4335 continue
4336
4337 meth = methods[0]
4338 inferred = next(meth.infer(context=context), None)
4339 if (
4340 isinstance(inferred, util.UninferableBase)
4341 or not inferred.callable()
4342 ):
4343 continue
4344
4345 context = copy_context(context)
4346 context.boundnode = operand
4347 context.callcontext = CallContext(args=[], callee=inferred)
4348
4349 call_results = inferred.infer_call_result(self, context=context)
4350 result = next(call_results, None)
4351 if result is None:
4352 # Failed to infer, return the same type.
4353 yield operand
4354 else:
4355 yield result
4356 except AttributeInferenceError as inner_exc:
4357 # The unary operation special method was not found.
4358 yield util.BadUnaryOperationMessage(operand, self.op, inner_exc)
4359 except InferenceError:
4360 yield util.Uninferable
4361
4362 @decorators.raise_if_nothing_inferred
4363 @decorators.path_wrapper
4364 def _infer(
4365 self: nodes.UnaryOp, context: InferenceContext | None = None, **kwargs: Any
4366 ) -> Generator[InferenceResult, None, InferenceErrorInfo]:
4367 """Infer what an UnaryOp should return when evaluated."""
4368 yield from self._filter_operation_errors(
4369 self._infer_unaryop, context, util.BadUnaryOperationMessage
4370 )
4371 return InferenceErrorInfo(node=self, context=context)

4678 ) -> Generator[InferenceResult, None, InferenceErrorInfo | None]:
4679 format_specs = Const("") if self.format_spec is None else self.format_spec
4680 uninferable_already_generated = False
4681 for format_spec in format_specs.infer(context, **kwargs):
4682 if not isinstance(format_spec, Const):
4683 if not uninferable_already_generated:
4684 yield util.Uninferable
4685 uninferable_already_generated = True
4686 continue

4689 if isinstance(value, Const):
4690 value_to_format = value.value
4691 try:
4692 formatted = format(value_to_format, format_spec.value)
4693 yield Const(
4694 formatted,
4695 lineno=self.lineno,
4696 col_offset=self.col_offset,
4697 end_lineno=self.end_lineno,
4698 end_col_offset=self.end_col_offset,
4699 )
4700 continue
4701 except (ValueError, TypeError):
4702 # happens when format_spec.value is invalid
4703 yield util.Uninferable
4704 uninferable_already_generated = True

4775
4776 @classmethod
4777 def _infer_from_values(
4778 cls, nodes: list[NodeNG], context: InferenceContext | None = None, **kwargs: Any
4779 ) -> Generator[InferenceResult, None, InferenceErrorInfo | None]:
4780 if not nodes:
4781 yield
4782 return
4783 if len(nodes) == 1:
4784 yield from nodes[0]._infer(context, **kwargs)
4785 return
4786 uninferable_already_generated = False
4787 for prefix in nodes[0]._infer(context, **kwargs):
4788 for suffix in cls._infer_from_values(nodes[1:], context, **kwargs):
4789 result = ""
4790 for node in (prefix, suffix):
4791 if isinstance(node, Const):
4792 result += str(node.value)
4793 continue
4794 result += MISSING_VALUE
4795 if MISSING_VALUE in result:
4796 if not uninferable_already_generated:
4797 uninferable_already_generated = True
4798 yield util.Uninferable
4799 else:
4800 yield Const(result)

5466# The _proxied attribute of all container types (List, Tuple, etc.)
5467# are set during bootstrapping by _astroid_bootstrapping().
5468CONST_CLS: dict[type, type[NodeNG]] = {
5469 list: List,
5470 tuple: Tuple,
5471 dict: Dict,
5472 set: Set,
5473 type(None): Const,
5474 type(NotImplemented): Const,
5475 type(...): Const,
5476 bool: Const,
5477 int: Const,
5478 float: Const,
5479 complex: Const,
5480 str: Const,
5481 bytes: Const,
5482}

5484
5485def _create_basic_elements(
5486 value: Iterable[Any], node: List | Set | Tuple
5487) -> list[NodeNG]:
5488 """Create a list of nodes to function as the elements of a new node."""
5489 elements: list[NodeNG] = []
5490 for element in value:
5491 element_node = const_factory(element)
5492 element_node.parent = node
5493 elements.append(element_node)
5494 return elements
5495
5496
5497def _create_dict_items(
5498 values: Mapping[Any, Any], node: Dict
5499) -> list[tuple[SuccessfulInferenceResult, SuccessfulInferenceResult]]:
5500 """Create a list of node pairs to function as the items of a new dict node."""
5501 elements: list[tuple[SuccessfulInferenceResult, SuccessfulInferenceResult]] = []
5502 for key, value in values.items():
5503 key_node = const_factory(key)
5504 key_node.parent = node
5505 value_node = const_factory(value)
5506 value_node.parent = node
5507 elements.append((key_node, value_node))
5508 return elements
5509
5510
5511def const_factory(value: Any) -> ConstFactoryResult:
5512 """Return an astroid node for a python value."""
5513 assert not isinstance(value, NodeNG)
5514
5515 # This only handles instances of the CONST types. Any
5516 # subclasses get inferred as EmptyNode.
5517 # TODO: See if we should revisit these with the normal builder.
5518 if value.__class__ not in CONST_CLS:
5519 node = EmptyNode()
5520 node.object = value
5521 return node
5522
5523 instance: List | Set | Tuple | Dict
5524 initializer_cls = CONST_CLS[value.__class__]
5525 if issubclass(initializer_cls, (List, Set, Tuple)):
5526 instance = initializer_cls(
5527 lineno=None,
5528 col_offset=None,
5529 parent=None,
5530 end_lineno=None,
5531 end_col_offset=None,
5532 )
5533 instance.postinit(_create_basic_elements(value, instance))
5534 return instance
5535 if issubclass(initializer_cls, Dict):
5536 instance = initializer_cls(
5537 lineno=None,
5538 col_offset=None,
5539 parent=None,
5540 end_lineno=None,
5541 end_col_offset=None,
5542 )
5543 instance.postinit(_create_dict_items(value, instance))
5544 return instance
5545 return Const(value)
